<inglise> Statement by the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni avaldus </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission notes the agreement of the European Parliament and the Council to provide for a regulatory procedure when considering the choice of projects, as opposed to the management procedure proposed by the Commission in the modified proposal following Parliament's second reading. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon p&ouml;&ouml;rab t&auml;helepanu sellele, et Euroopa Parlament ja n&otilde;ukogu on kokku leppinud n&auml;ha projektide valimisel ette regulatiivkomitee menetlus vastandina komisjonile, kelle ettepanek on kasutada parlamendi teise lugemise j&auml;rel muudetud ettepaneku puhul korralduskomitee menetlust. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission insists, as it stated at the time of the adoption of the Common Position, on the importance of applying the criteria of Article 2 of Council Decision 1999/468/EC of 28 June 1999, laying down the procedures for the exercise of implementing powers conferred on the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon toonitab, et nagu ta juba m&auml;rkis &uuml;hisseisukoha vastuv&otilde;tmise ajal, on v&auml;ga t&auml;htis kohaldada komisjoni rakendusvolituste kasutamise menetlust kehtestava n&otilde;ukogu 28. juuni 1999. aasta otsuse 1999/468/E&Uuml; artiklis 2 nimetatud kriteeriume. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission believes that, the choice of projects being a measure with substantial budgetary implications, this should follow the management procedure. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon usub, et projekti valikul tuleb kasutada korralduskomitee menetlust, sest projektide valimisel on oluline m&otilde;ju eelarvele. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission considers that to ignore the terms of Article 2 of Decision 1999/468/EC in a case as clear as this is contrary to both the spirit and the letter of the Council Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon leiab, et otsuse 1999/468/E&Uuml; artikli 2 tingimuste eiramine isegi nii selgel juhul kui k&auml;esolev on vastuolus nimetatud n&otilde;ukogu otsuse m&otilde;tte ja s&auml;ttega. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission must therefore reserve its position in this matter, including its right to take appropriate future action before the Court. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu peab komisjon j&auml;&auml;ma selles asjas oma seisukohale, kaasa arvatud &otilde;igus esitada asi hiljem Euroopa Kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise> Statement by the Council </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu avaldus </eesti>
<inglise> The Council notes the statement by the Commission regarding the choice of the committee procedure for the adoption, by the Commission, of implementing measures under the LIFE Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu p&ouml;&ouml;rab t&auml;helepanu komisjoni avaldusele komiteemenetluse valimise kohta LIFE-m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel rakendusmeetmete vastuv&otilde;tmisel. </eesti>
<inglise> In choosing the regulatory procedure contained in Article 5 of Council Decision 1999/468/EC of 28 June 1999, laying down the procedures for the exercise of implementing powers conferred on the Commission, the Council took into account the experience gained with the regulatory procedure under the LIFE instrument during the first (since 1992) and second phase (since 1996) and the nature of the LIFE instrument, which plays a vital role in the protection of the environment within the Community and contributes to the implementation and development of Community environmental policy. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni rakendusvolituste kasutamise menetlust kehtestava n&otilde;ukogu 28. juuni 1999. aasta otsuse 1999/468/E&Uuml; artiklis 5 nimetatud regulatiivkomitee menetluse valimisel v&otilde;ttis n&otilde;ukogu arvesse regulatiivkomitee menetlusega LIFE-rahastamisvahendi t&ouml;&ouml;s esimesel etapil (alates 1992. aastast) ja teisel etapil (alates 1996. aastast) omandatud kogemusi ja LIFE-rahastamisvahendi laadi, millel on t&auml;htis osa &uuml;henduse keskkonna kaitsmisel ning mis aitab kaasa &uuml;henduse keskkonnapoliitika teostamisele ja arendamisele. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council recalls that the criteria laid down in Article 2 of Decision 1999/468/EC are legally non-binding and of an illustrative nature. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu tuletab meelde, et otsuse 1999/468/E&Uuml; artiklis 2 nimetatud kriteeriumid ei ole &otilde;iguslikult siduvad, vaid selgitavad. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council considers that the scope of the implementing powers in this Regulation fully justify having recourse to a regulatory procedure. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu leiab, et selles m&auml;&auml;ruses esitatud rakendusvolituste ulatus &otilde;igustab t&auml;ielikult regulatiivkomitee menetluse kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Statement by the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni avaldus </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission states that before fixing annually the dates for the submission of proposals, it will check, their feasibility with the relevant committees. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teatab, et enne iga-aastast ettepanekute esitamise kuup&auml;evade kinnitamist kontrollib ta asjaomastes komiteedes nende teostatavust. </eesti>
 